
 
# Notes on the thesis progress
- Everything is online (including the thesis defence), unless you wish otherwise
Timeline:
- Start
- Registration
- Thesis writing (between one and two months)
- Thesis submission
- Thesis defence (at least one week or 10 days after the submission)
## Start
- Two documents are needed: CV + up-to-date transcript
## Tips for experiments
- The experiments should be reproducible at the end of your thesis. Fixing seeds is recommended.
- Consistency is key in experiments, especially to compare results. Explicitly reporting:
  - Dataset/language selection
  - Model selection (and awareness of their training; e.g., was the model pre-trained on the language?)
  - Hyperparameter settings
  
- It is better to keep track of the licence of the datasets and language resources that are used.
## Mid-term document for the registration
This is just for internal purposes (NOT graded). This serves both for you and me to keep track of what has been done.
- Small literature review: Five (or more) articles that you have read in a few sentences (what is it about? why is it relevant for your thesis?)
- Summary of the methodology (datasets, models); bullet points are enough
- Presenting the results: tables and figures; no need to analyse in depth
## Registration
Details in: https://collab.dvb.bayern/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=TUMcit&title=Abschlussarbeiten
Information needed: the thesis title + your matriculation number
## On the usage of AI tools
We follow the ACL policy on that point: https://2023.aclweb.org/blog/ACL-2023-policy/
## Thesis writing
LaTeX template: https://github.com/TUM-Dev/tum-thesis-latex
More information: https://www.cit.tum.de/en/cit/studies/students/thesis-completing-your-studies/informatics/
- For bachelor's theses: around 30 pages
- For master's theses: around 60 pages 
- Discuss the thesis structure
There are three tiers in the template: 
1. Chapter
1.1 Section
1.1.1 Subsection
- Two rounds of proof-reading, if time allows: one per chapter/section, one at the end for the overall coherence
- The file name should be clear.
## Thesis defence (estimate)
- For bachelor's theses: 10-15 min of presentation and 10-15 min of questions 
- For master's theses: 15 min of presentation and 15-20 min of questions 
